In this speech, President Trump addresses a gathering at the United States Holocaust Memorial Museum. He expresses his gratitude to the survivors of the Holocaust and pays tribute to the victims. Trump condemns those who deny the Holocaust and promises to confront anti-Semitism and prejudice. He emphasizes the importance of remembering the Holocaust and vows to always stand with the Jewish people and support Israel. The president concludes by sharing the story of Gerda Klein, a survivor who found hope and love after liberation. He emphasizes the power of light and truth to overcome darkness and evil. Trump ends by pledging to never forget and to ensure that justice prevails.